==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Besom
<hw>Be"som</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>besme</ets>, <ets>besum</ets>, AS. <ets>besma</ets>; akin to D.
<ets>bezem</ets>, OHG <ets>pesamo</ets>, G. <ets>besen</ets>; of
uncertain origin.]</ety> <def>A brush of twigs for sweeping; a broom;
anything which sweeps away or destroys.</def> <mark>[Archaic or
Fig.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will sweep it with the <qex>besom</qex> of destruction.</q>
<rj><qau>Isa. xiv. 23.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The housemaid with her <qex>besom</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Irving.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Besom</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Besom
<hw>Be"som</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Besomed</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To sweep, as with
a besom.</def> <mark>[Archaic or Poetic]</mark>
<rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Rolls back all Greece, and <qex>besoms</qex> wide the plain.</q>
<rj><qau>Barlow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Besomer</ent>⟦br⟧
